The paper focuses on using convolutional neural networks for person search, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of multi-task learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on a dataset, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the use of region proposal networks and multiple loss functions, which are techniques commonly used in information retrieval, falling under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
